{"serial": "12010", "department_serial": 11, "code": "EL2033", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Introduction to Film Studies", "ch": "電影研究概論"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Yau Ching"], "ch": ["游靜"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 3, "session": ["6", "7", "8"]}, "loc": {"building": "A", "room": "110"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "英美語文學系", "en": "Department of English"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 38, "selected": 0, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "學習解讀電影語言之風格運用， 如鏡頭、剪接、\n音樂或場面調度（包括燈光、空間、佈景、服裝、化妝、顏色與電影劇情的內部關係）等元素；\n學習解讀電影隱含之意識形態；\n學習了解不同地域電影與地緣政治之關係\n學習分析世界電影與華語電影之互文關係\n提升欣賞電影的鑑賞力，有助同學在電影創作與評論方面的發展。", "en": "¥To develop a familiarity with trends in world cinema—from changing modes of film production to developments in film theory\n¥To examine how key ways of understanding film culture (e.g., aesthetics, authorship, genre, film movements, national cinema) have been reexamined in light of current changes in world cinema\n¥To explore the various ways in which films create meanings against the backdrop of global film history\n¥To appreciate the ways in which films cross various “borders”—including ethnic, racial, linguistic, cultural, as well as national borders\n¥To understand why many of the most influential critical theorists of our era have turned to the film medium as a way of exploring broader philosophical, social, or cultural issues"}, "outline": {"ch": "1. 電影語言及電影美學發展的過程；\n2. 認識重要電影類型的分別和發展；\n3. 認識和欣賞世界各地電影史（尤其第三世界）和流派；\n4. 電影語言之風格運用， 如鏡頭、剪接、音樂或場面調度（包括燈光、空間、佈景、服裝、化妝、顏色與電影劇情的內部關係）等元素；\n5. 電影隱含之意識形態及與地緣政治的關係（如台灣電影與冷戰）；\n6. 世界電影與華語電影（含中、港、台）之互文關係", "en": "This course seeks to help students understand how a film conveys its meanings by surveying key developments and debates in cinema studies. It introduces various critical methods and tools including but not limited to notions of realism and modernity, formal analysis and textual studies, genre studies, ideological and feminist film criticisms. You are also introduced to various ways of looking at cinema: as technology, an art form, a “language”, as well as an industry, a consumer product and cultural formation. Films of various genres from Europe, US, Asia and the former Soviet Union are used as study materials. Through this course, you are expected to develop a stronger sensitivity towards cultural histories in different parts of the world, and more skills to discuss issues of representation and the visually dominated culture in our world today."}, "textbook": {"ch": "https://filmanalysis.yale.edu/mise-en-scene/", "en": "Barbara Creed and Jeanette Hoorn, “Memory and History: Early Film, Colonialism and the French Civilising Mission in Indochina,” Early Film and Colonialism in French Indochina.\nWanderings of Three-Hairs the Orphan 三毛流浪記 (Zhao Ming and Yan Gong, China, 1949)\nChristopher Rea, “Wanderings of Three-Hairs the Orphan.” Chinese Film Classics, 1922–1949. New York: Columbia University Press, 2021, pp. 256-274."}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "100%", "en": "100%"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "學生課上出席不足者將被扣分。\n學生上課（含電影放映）應準時出席，遲到 10 分鐘即算缺席，早退需向老師作出合理解釋。\n上課（包括看電影時）應遵守課堂安靜及不用3C等守則。\n學生需要依時遞交作業，遲交即被扣分。作業必須全部由自己完成。所有依賴他人或非人完成的作業將被打零分。", "en": "Continuous assessment30％\nClass presentations 30％\nFilm analysis40％\n1. Completion of course readings and active participation in class discussions and presentations. Attendance in lectures, screenings and group discussions.\n2. Readiness to present a summary and the key arguments of the weekly readings whenever called upon.\n3. Submission of film analysis of the required length on time."}, "officeHour": {"ch": "Wed 1-2, 5-6 （by appointment)", "en": "Wed 1-2, 5-6 （by appointment)"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"c